OL,4,CNew police CCTV use rules criticised as
OL,5,Cbare bones
OL,6, A proposed code of practice covering
OL,7, police use of live facial recognition
OL,8, in England and Wales has been
OL,9, criticised by human rights groups.
OL,11,FLive facial-recognition systems compare
OL,12,Ffaces captured on closed-circuit
OL,13,Ftelevision with those on a watch-list,
OL,14,Falerting officers to a match.
OL,16,FFormer CCTV watchdog Tony Porter said
OL,17,Fthe new rules were "bare bones" and
OL,18,Foffered unclear guidance.
OL,20,FAnd two campaign groups have called for
OL,21,Fthe practice to be ended entirely.
